args: What? The seeds of the abyss can\nbe controlled using Vania's blood?
I can't speak to the truth of it, but our\nimperial friends certainly think so.
Alone, those seeds are far more than man\ncan handle, so they think to fight fire with\nfire. Neutralize one poison with another.
If they COULD be controlled, the seeds\nwould be a weapon without peer. And I\nsay that from personal experience.
That doesn't make it okay to take a lady's\nblood and use it on some slimy tentacle\nthing. Have a little class, jeez!
Agreed. What's more, if it's solely her\nblood they're after, she may be as useful\nto them dead as alive.
I say we leave Vania in the safety of the\nHalidom and set out to destroy those seeds\nas soon as possible.
We might, if we knew their location.\nBut our intelligence source went silent\njust after we learned of all this.
They probably went on high alert after\nlearning that we've started guarding her.
It's oddâ€”they never seemed quite so\ncareful until now. If anything, they were\nhasty. Desperate.
Hmph. Perhaps some third party stepped\nin to guide them. In any case, taking the\ninitiative to strike first isn't an option.
But neither can we sit idle while they hold\nthose seeds. It's quite the conundrum.
Is it, though? We just dangle me out there\nas bait and grab 'em when they show up.
However sneaky they're trying to be,\nthey won't turn down a chance like that.\nBoom, easy.
Maybe so, but I don't... No. I can't allow it.\nThe risk is too great. It's tantamount to\nwillingly walking into their trap.
And there you go treating me like a child\nagain. I will be FINE, thankyouverymuch!
You watched me beat that nasty ol' dragon\nbefore, didn't you?
I did. But didn't you say the trueblood\npowers you used then were only\ntemporary?
Okay, so I'm not QUITE that strong right\nnow, but I'm still unstoppable when I put\nmy game face on!
She says she can handle it.\nWhy not take her at her word?
We've all seen that she's a capable fighter.\nAnd frankly, we haven't many alternatives,\nnor the luxury of waiting.

They may set a trap, but what's safer
than luring them to a fortified position? 
Or would you rather allow them free use
of the seeds?
Fine. But we don't go in without a solid\nplan. Is that understood, Vania?
Duh. Obviously. Okay, time to show you\nwhat I can do when I put my mind to it!
The Day of the Decoy Operation\nThoroughfare
All right. We'll be nearby, as discussed.\nThe moment you feel in danger, fall back.
I know, I know. Just use my powers to lure\nthem out, right? I'll be fiiine. Go and hide\nalready!
He's such a worrywart.\nNow, let's do this!
Guess I'll start with some neighborhood\nfiends. Time to get wrecked!
...Anybody want to show up yet? No? Ugh.\nIf they're not coming, I'm just going home.
That wouldn't do at all. We're running short\non time. We need the trueblood now.
You know our orders, men:\ntake her by any means necessary!
Finally, the bad guys turn up! But did you\nreally think I'd lose to an ambush I saw\ncoming?
Let's go, bloodkin! Sparky, Slimy, you too!
Right! I'll stay at Vania's side.\nYou two watch the rear!
Leave it to us! Echo forth, thunder's roar!
Out come the knights in shining armor.\nNo matter. Crush them all, men! Attack!
Drop the useless bravado! Do you really\nthink to overcome our numbers?!
Rgh... There ARE more of them than\nlast time.
But it would take more still to best a\nKnight of Levin!
*sigh* Then I suppose I ought to put some\neffort in as wellâ€”Tentacle Phantasma!
Whoaaa, NICE! Not bad, you two!
Impressive as ever. Now let's stay focused\nand play our part. Blazing Circlet!
You got it. Have a little taste of what a\nvampire can do!
Heh heh. This is what you get for coming\nat me! Now, weapons on the floor. Get\nthose hands over your heads!
Nrgh... A vampire's abilities are truly\nterrifying. But our resolve is greater still!
Huh? Wait, hold up, just what are youâ€”
Seed of the abyss!\nTake this body as your sustenance!
Now is the hour to unleash your awesome\nmight upon the world! Devour the\ntrueblood, and claim her power!
Lord Phares! Bear witness to my resolve!\nNraaaOOOOOOORGH!
No! The seed of the abyss is stirring! Once\nit wakes, it will begin devouring all life in\nthe area to fuel its rampage!
And the fool who used it will be consumed,\nbecoming a mindless puppet of wanton\ndestruction.
Eeagh?! Wh-why is it coming THIS way?!\nS-stop! Please, don'tâ€”!
Nooo! I don't want to die!\nEat them if you have to, not ME!
Ewww! Now something gross is sprouting\nout of that old guy, too. We've gotta stop\nit!
Right. The seed must be destroyed and\npried loose of its host as soon as possible.\nI'm afraid it won't be that simple, though.
It's absorbing them all and growing at a\nterrifying rate! Rrgh... We can't get close\nenough to attack!
Damn. It's nearly devoured them all.\nIt will soon turn its attentions to us!\nIt... It's coming for me!
Aaagh! Ow ow ow... That really HURT!
Damnable seed! It's drinking the blood\nfrom her wound just now!
I can feel its power surging from here.\nAll that, after just a few drops. Her blood\nis as terrifying a catalyst as they say.
Are you all right?! Why did you take that\nblow for me? You're the one they're after!
It's only natural I would. After all,\nI'm your...mistress, bloodkin.
It's only right that I protect you. Plus...
How am I supposed to forge a bond with\nyou if I don't prove I'm strong enough to\ndeserve your trust?
Vania... Was that weighing on you this\nwhole time? Is that why you...?
I'm sorry. You may be right that I haven't\nfully trusted in your strength until now.\nMy urge to protect you was a selfish one.
You really are incredibly strong. You're\nevery bit my equal, and all this time,\nyou've only wanted to be seen as such.
I finally understand that. Vania... I'm\nclearly not the quickest learner, but can\nwe start anew? This time as trusted peers?
I thought you'd never ask. A bloodkin and\nhis vampire are unstoppable because of\nthe super strong bond they share!
Now what do you say we prove it?\nListen to me for once and let's kick\nthat thing's slimy butt!
Right! The seed must be destroyed. And\nwe'll see it done, by our combined might!
